H3.text: Which European country hosted the 1956 Winter Olympic Games. ItalY

A4.text: The 1956 Winter Olympics were held in Cortina d'Ampezzo, Italy, from 26 January to 5 February 1956.

A5.text: Cortina d'Ampezzo, Italy, was awarded the 1956 Winter Olympics, beating out Montreal, Colorado Springs, and Lake Placid.
